                    <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/2822</idno>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" source="#bib2822-1" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/authors">Rabban Sliba (father of <persName>Rabban Joshua</persName>) was a monastic
                        author who composed a martyrology in the late thirteenth century or early
                        fourteenth century (some time after the death of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/239">Bar ʿEbroyo</persName>). One source
                        describes him as being from <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/217">Ḥaḥ</placeName>.</note>
